voiphandset (0.2.2-1) oracular; urgency=medium

  * Fix: ring engine now plays through PipeWire (paplay) instead of
    direct kernel ALSA. The PipeWire loopback module that backs the
    speakerphone virtual sink holds the kernel device exclusively, so
    aplay's plughw access was failing silently.

 -- Jason Jorgenson <jjorgenson@gmail.com>  Tue, 12 May 2026 13:25:00 +0000

voiphandset (0.2.1-1) oracular; urgency=medium

  * Fix: D-Bus name registration broke because BecomeMonitor() was being
    called on the same connection that owned the service name, putting
    it into read-only mode. Now uses two private SessionBus connections.
  * Fix: ring engine notifies the router when it finishes naturally, so
    call_state correctly returns to IDLE.
  * PipeWire loopback target updated to the iec958-stereo profile name.

 -- Jason Jorgenson <jjorgenson@gmail.com>  Tue, 12 May 2026 13:15:00 +0000

voiphandset (0.2.0-1) oracular; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Refactor into voiphandset Python package; install handset script.
  * Add D-Bus IPC interface (com.arkygeek.Handset).
  * Add PipeWire loopback config for "HP Handset (Speakerphone)" sink.
  * Add call-state machine (idle/ringing/handset/holding/speakerphone).
  * Auto bit-0 routing based on cradle state and PipeWire stream activity.
  * Ring on incoming Rambox WhatsApp calls (US ring); Messenger burst
    heuristic (UK ring) for 3-in-10s notifications.

 -- Jason Jorgenson <jjorgenson@gmail.com>  Tue, 12 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
